<section class="section bg-white">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row g-5">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <div class="course-content-block" data-aos="fade-up">
          <h2>About the Program</h2>
          <p>
            The General Nursing &amp; Midwifery (G.N.M.) diploma is a three-year
            program that prepares students for a career in general nursing and
            midwifery. It combines theoretical coursework with hands-on clinical
            training at our affiliated teaching hospital.
          </p>
          <p>
            Graduates of this program are eligible to register with the Gujarat
            Nursing Council and work as staff nurses across hospitals, clinics
            and community health centres.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="course-content-block" data-aos="fade-up">
          <h2>Eligibility Criteria</h2>
          <ul class="course-list">
            <li>Passed 10+2 or equivalent from a recognised board</li>
            <li>Minimum 40% aggregate marks</li>
            <li>
              Minimum age of 17 years as on 31st December of admission year
            </li>
            <li>Must have passed English as a core/elective subject</li>
            <li>Medically fit as per Gujarat Nursing Council norms</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="course-content-block" data-aos="fade-up">
